an> <span class="nav-next"><a href="http://www.gbopera.it/2011/04/das-rheingold-at-the-met/" rel="next">&#8220;Das Rheingold&#8221; at the Met <span class="meta-nav">&rarr;</span></a></span> </nav><nav class="nav-single-hidden"> <span class="nav-previous"></span> <span class="nav-next"></span><div class="clear"></div> </nav></div><div class="comments-block box-shadow-2px clearfix"><div id="comments" class="comments-area"><h2 class="comments-title"> 1 comment</h2><ol class="commentlist"><li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="li-comment-8463"> <article id="comment-8463" class="comment clearfix"> <header class="comment-meta comment-author vcard"><div class="comment-avatar"><img src="http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/0bc3e046f65a1ce38ffa5a50642ff82f?s=75&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g" width="75" height="75" alt="" class="avatar avatar-75wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-75 alignnone photo avatar-default" /></div><cite class="fn">stuart</cite><a class="comment-meta-time muted-small" href="http://www.gbopera.it/2011/04/metropolitan-operadas-rheingold/#comment-8463"><time datetime="2011-04-08T02:48:04+00:00">8 aprile 2011 at 02:48</time></a> </header> <section class="comment-content comment"><p>Think you should look into Matthias Wohlbrecht as Mime and Loge, a part from the fact he has the voice for these parts he is one of the best singing actors on the scene today. He is now making a big name for himself for all comprimario parts from the witch in Hansel Und Gretel to Loge and Mime, and has recenly added Herodes to his repertoire. Unfortunately he does not have much on youtube at the moment, but while on stage you can&#8217;t take your eyes off him he is such a wonderful singing actor, rarely seen these days.</p> </section><div class="reply clearfix"></div> </article></li></ol><div id="respond" class="comment-respond"><h3 id="reply-title" class="comment-reply-title">Lascia un commento <small><a rel="nofollow" id="cancel-comment-reply-link" href="/2011/04/metropolitan-operadas-rhei